args: I should leave the castle.\nIt's better this way.
*huff* *huff* I'm glad I made it in time.
What's with this letter you left behind?\nWhy are you going back to your homeland?
Because my being in the castle is nothing\nbut a burden to others.
Like how I was taken in by those ne'er-do-\nwells the other day and ended up making\nlots of trouble for everyone.
I may have left my home, but nothing has\nreally changed.
It's all well and good to give your all for\nyour dreams, but you need to be a little\nmore aware of what's going on around you.
Maybe you ought to quit being\nirresponsible and face reality.
I calmed myself down and took a look\naround me, and I realized the truth:\nIn the end, dreams are just that.
That's why I figured it was time for me to\nforget about skating and go back home to\nbecome a true warrior.
After all, it doesn't matter how hard I try;\nmy dream will never come true.
I don't think that's true at all.\nIn fact, look behind you.
Hey, mister! Show us that thing you did\nwhere you slide around the ice!
Looks like there are plenty of people\ninterested in your talent.
Thanks for saving me the other day,\nmister!
Ah. You were held captive by the brigands\nas well, yes?
You were so cool! You were like KA-ZOOM\nand then you went WHAM and all the bad\npeople were like AAAARRRGGH!
Even though we were captured, your\nsunny attitude helped us through that\nmost dark time.
Hey! I wanna try that, too! Tell me how!\nC'mon, tell me!
I'm so moved by your words...
Oh, and Orsem? Elisanne telling you to be\nmore aware of what's around you wasn't\nher blaming you for anything.
I mean, sure, she wants you to face reality,\nbut that's not ALL she was saying.
You're forthright to a fault, and if you're \nnot careful, you could end up getting hurt.\nShe just doesn't want that to happen.
You mean like when I was kidnapped.
Exactly. And Orsem, you ARE fulfilling your\ndream, even if slowly.
That's why you don't need to rush headlong\ninto things and do it all at once.
There are already lots of people around\nyou who are becoming skating fanatics,\nafter all.
You see? Take an even closer look.
...I get it now. I was in such haste to make\nmy dream a reality that I didn't stop to\nlook at what was already around me.
There are so many people interested in\nlearning about my beloved skating...
Orsem, I'm not a prince with lots of power\nand influence like my brothers.
But as your friend, I still want to help you\nmake your dream a reality.
So let's do it together. What do you say?
Aaaah ha ha! I've been such a dope!
I just hadn't realized the truth that I'm\nnot alone anymore.
And that won't do! I have to tell each and\nevery one of these people about the magic\nof gliding across the ice!
With this many future fanatics gathered,\nI'm going to need even more blades!
Just a moment while I go fetch them.\nEveryone else, meet me in the courtyard!
Ta-daaah! Let our deep dive into the art\nof the foot blades begin!
First, attach the blades to your shoes and\nstand on the ground.
That's it. Now alternate back and forth\nwith your feet. Ready...go! Left! Right!\nLeft! Right!
Guy's explanations have gotten a lot\nbetter, yeah?
Indeed. But they're still full of his\ntrademark vigor.
Everyone truly looks to be enjoying\nthemselves.
Hey, don't just stand there watching!\nCome hit the ice already!
I can't even begin to tell you how happy\nI am right now.
But next time, it's my turn to help YOU\nachieve YOUR dreams!
Thanks, Orsem. I can't wait to see what\nthe future holds for us.
